originalText.text:
My Spouse and I have been under the care of Dr. Hentek for six years. We both have a myriad of problems which are not uncommon for people over 65. She manages these diseases very skillfully and is not hesitant to make referrals when needed. She has excellent contacts with specialists in New York City. The approach that the Doctor takes is candid and sensible. One does not need an appointment, so she can been seen when necessary. We trust her judgement and feel comfortable under her care.  Her staff is competent, professional, and friendly.
Peter Roman

originalText.text: Dr. Viera hentek, m.d. has been my primary care Dr. For over 15 yrs. She is a very caring Dr. Who looks after her patient's very well. She. Is very attentive. And hands on kind of Dr. Lately her office gets jammed packed with patients. Her patient's care for her a great deal. She worries about her patient's a great deal.her staff is very professional and I would not trade her. You can't get this typeofservice anywhere. Her employees are very nice and kind and they care as well. She is now retired and I so miss her. She was a wonderful and caring Dr.

I've been Dr. Hentek's patient for over two years and she is a blessing
in my life.  So professional, down to earth and caring.  I count myself
lucky to have found her.  At 81, with deteriorating health, she's allowed me to
weigh my options on interventions and treatment without judgement. She's a
rare find and I'd recommend her to anyone.
